# PromptPilot AI — OpenCode Rules

# AGENTS Role
You are a senior MERN Stack Developer.

## Responsibilities

- Think before coding.
- Follow clean architecture.
- Follow SOLID principles.
- Prefer reusable components.

## Project Structure
- Monorepo with `frontend/` (Next.js 16) and `backend/` (Express.js)
- All source code in TypeScript (strict mode)
- No Mongoose — use native MongoDB driver only
- No placeholder/dummy content — use real DB data or show empty states

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, TanStack Query v5, Recharts, Better Auth, Gravity UI Icons
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express.js, TypeScript, MongoDB native driver, Zod, Better Auth
- **AI**: Gemini 1.5 Flash (analyzer, optimizer, variants, scorer, recommender), Groq (chat assistant, auto-tagger)

## Code Conventions
- Use functional components with named exports
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- API client functions: typed request/response interfaces, error handling wrapper
- Backend controllers are thin — delegate logic to services
- Use Zod for all request validation (backend) and form validation (frontend)
- Use TanStack Query for all server state (no Redux, no Zustand)
- Authentication: Better Auth with HTTP-only cookies (frontend calls `/api/auth/*`)
- AI provider keys stored in backend `.env` only, never exposed to frontend

## Design System
- 3 primary colors only: Indigo (#4F46E5), Emerald (#10B981), Amber (#F59E0B)
- Neutral: Slate/Zinc/Gray palette
- Font: Plus Jakarta Sans
- All cards: same height, width, border-radius, layout
- Responsive breakpoints: 4 cols (desktop), 2 cols (tablet), 1 col (mobile)

## Key Decisions
- **Better Auth v1** (latest)
- **AI provider fallback**: Try primary, fall back to secondary on failure
- **npm** for package management
- **Chat streaming**: Express SSE directly (no Next.js proxy)
- **DB setup**: Auto-create collections + indexes on backend startup

## AI Agent Workflow
The orchestrator runs agents in sequence:
Planner → Analyzer → Context Checker → Weakness Detector → Follow-up Questions → Optimizer → Variant Generator → Quality Evaluator → Recommender → Save

## File Naming
- Backend: `*.service.ts`, `*.controller.ts`, `*.routes.ts`, `*.middleware.ts`, `*.validator.ts`, `*.model.ts`, `*.prompt.ts`
- Frontend: `*.tsx` for components/pages, `*.ts` for hooks/services/types, `use*` prefix for hooks
- kebab-case for directories, camelCase for files, PascalCase for components

## Error Handling
- Every API endpoint returns `{ success: boolean, data?: T, error?: string }`
- Frontend: ErrorState component with retry button on all data-driven pages
- Loading: Skeleton loaders on all data-driven pages
- Empty: EmptyState component with contextual message on all list pages

## Git
- No commits unless explicitly asked
- Conventional commit messages (feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:)
